Citation.sAbstract: The psuedo ternary LLE data are reported for the following systems at 298.15 K: an aqueous  sulfuric acid solution (ASS) + dodecane + tributylphosphate (TBP); an ASS + 1-dodecanol + TBP; an  ASS + undecane + TBP; an ASS + dodecane + trioctylamine (TOA); an ASS + 1-dodecanol + TOA and an  ASS + undecane + TOA. These experimental LLE data were correlated well with the non-random twoliquid  (NRTL) GE model. In addition, the density ( ) and the refractive index (nD) for the systems  {TBP + dodecane},  {TBP + 1-dodecanol},  {TBP + undecane},  {TOA + dodecane},  {TOA + 1-dodecanol}  and  {TOA + undecane}  at 298.15 K were determined. These data were used to calculate the binary excess  molar volumes (VE) and the deviations of the refractive indices ( R) over the entire composition range.  The experimental data were satisfactorily fitted using the Redlich Kister polynomial.
Citation.sTitle: Liquid-liquid equilibria for aqueous sulfuric acid solutions with undecane, dodecane, or 1-dodecanol, trioctylamine or tributyl  phosphate and excess and deviation properties for sub-binary systems at 298.15 K
